    - History of Aethermoor new
        
        The history of Aethermere is written in blood, suffering, and pain. But as the old cycle goes, after years of war, the continent once again found peace.
        
        Aethermere flourished, divided among five great kingdoms. With the guidance of the gods, its people prospered for generations. Crops grew in abundance, illness was cured, and knowledge, both arcane and scientific, advanced beyond anything their ancestors had imagined.
        
        It should have been enough.
        
        But mortal greed, jealousy, and hunger for more knew no limits. Despite their wealth and stability—despite peace treaties and overflowing abundance—the five kings sought more. More power. More control. More influence over one another.
        
        And so the cycle began again.
        
        What followed was the most devastating war in Aethermere’s history. Centuries of peace had allowed kingdoms to grow unchecked—larger armies, stronger magic, deadlier inventions. When war came, it came with unimaginable force. Cities burned. Millions died.
        
        Magic and science, once used to sustain life, were twisted into weapons of annihilation. The land itself was scarred, poisoned until nothing could grow, the skies choked with ash until the sun was little more than a memory. Mortals had gained power beyond their control, and they used it to destroy everything. One line crossed after another. 
        
        Even the gods were horrified. In the face of such ruin, they made a final decree: they would abandon Aethermere. Mortals no longer deserver their gifts and guidance. They had squandered every chance that had been given.
        
        But the worst was yet to come. In their desperation for victory, mortals unleashed their deadliest creation, the Scourge Curse. A plague unlike any before it. It spread without mercy, killing the living with sickness and agony. Those consumed by it rose again, as twisted, soulless creatures with pitch-black eyes, driven only to kill and spread the curse further.
        
        This marked the beginning of the end.
        
        After this, Aethermere lay as a wasteland. The war ended, not because people found reason, but because there was no one left to continue it. The five kingdoms collapsed, one after another, leaving behind only scattered provinces, broken cities, and desperate villages.
        
        Those who survived fought for every day of their existances. They scrapped over resources, protected themselves from bandits and the plague.
        
        In those times of despair, a young elven man from the Argon Province rose to power, determined to change things. He dreamed of restoring the continent to its former peace and prosperity, a place where people could live instead of merely survive.
        
        Soldiers, outcasts, and broken lords, all began to follow him and unite under his banner. His cause was noble, his vision compelling, and many rallied behind him. But this man was not without flaw. Where words failed, he used force. He crushed every resistance and paved his road to unity with bloodshed and death.
        
        Decades later, he succeeded. Nearly all of Aethermere stood under a single banner, the Kingdom of Argon. United, they pushed back against the Scourge and sought to reclaim what had been lost.
        
        For centuries, Malvek ruled. He conqured, ended wars and held the kingdom together. But there were enemies his sword could not defeat.
        
        The land remained scarred and largely uninhabitable. The skies stayed dark as the sun was hidden behind endless clouds. Hunger and disease still claimed many lives. And worst of all the Scourge Curse endured.
        
    - History of Argon
        
        The Kingdom of Argon was the first in known history to unite all of Aethermere under a single rule, that of Malvek Dawnheart. To some, he was a savior who brought order to a broken world. To others, a tyrant who conquered it through bloodshed. The truth is rarely so simple. A man of such power and legacy is bound to inspire both loyalty and hatred. To rise so high, he must have crossed others, deceived them, and committed injustices of his own.
        
        His true challenge though came when he had to face the Scourge. Malvek found a way to destroy this plague for good, saving the Aetheremere. He spent all of his time and resources on this mission and the only the history will know he succeeded.
        
